DISPLAY TYPES
= block vs. inline

BLOCK = movements stack vertically; take full width
- ex: <div>, <p>, <h1>, <ul>, <li>, <section>

INLINE = movements flow side by side; similar to words in a sentence
- ex: <span>, <a>, <strong>, <img>

centering an image:

img {
  display: block;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

Change to block first, then auto margins work

Pseudo-classes = Interactive Styles

mouse hovers over a link:

a:hover {
  color: red;
  text-decoration: underline;
}

an input is focused:
input:focus {
  border-color: blue;
  outline: none;
}

first and last child elements:
li:first-child { font-weight: bold; }
li:last-child { color: gray; }

CSS transitions: be sure to pair :hover with transition for a polished, professional feel.